cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.FL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with lambda calculus, which is a fundamental topic in mathematical logic and computer science. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper introduces an extension of the lambda calculus, which is a core concept in programming language theory. 
- cs.TL (Temporal Logic) is a possible category as the paper introduces a unary symbol τ used to witness the β-steps needed in the normalization to the Bohm Tree, which can be seen as a temporal aspect of the lambda calculus. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the normal forms of lambda terms, which can be seen as a language recognition problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper introduces a new data structure, the clocked Bohm Tree, which can be used to discriminate lambda terms.
